         <abstract>
            <p>An algorithm is given for the computation of the recessive solution of a second-order linear difference equation, based upon a combination of algorithms due to J. C. P. Miller and F. W. J. Olver. A special feature is automatic and rigorous control of truncation error. The method is illustrated by application to the well-used example of the Bessel functions $J_r(x)$.</p>
          </abstract>
